[Malaria is prevalent in the eastern part of Bolivar State, including
Las Claritas and La Paragua located south of the Guri water
reservoir. Most diamond mining in this area is done illegally by
individuals under primitive conditions. Under such conditions it is
not surprising that malaria is a problem in an endemic area.

An interesting article on diamond mining in the Bolivar State of
Venezuela can be found at
<http://www.pacweb.org/Documents/diamonds_KP/16_thelostworld_Eng-Nov2006.pdf>.

Maps of Venezuela are available at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/venezuela.gif>
and the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/0d*O>.
A map of the Bolivar State can be found at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bol%C3%ADvar_State> Mod.EP]
